<p class="">May I ask the Prime Minister how the Minister of Works will know anything at all about the industrial activities on atomic energy? Is he to be associated with the work of the Lord President of the Council in this matter, because, otherwise, it would appear that the answers will be made by a Minister having no responsibility for and no connection whatever with this enterprise? Would it not be very much better if the Minister of Supply were to answer both on the industrial and the weapon side of this business?</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
